article.headline: E. Washington 71, UC Santa Barbara 70
article.story: SANTA BARBARA (AP) -- Rodney Stuckey scored 21 of his 30 points in the second half to rally Eastern Washington for a 71-70 victory over UC Santa Barbara Saturday in a Bracket Busters game. Stuckey made just 3 of 10 shots in the first half as UC Santa Barbara took a 29-28 lead. The sophomore guard rallied the Eagles by scoring 10 points in the final 6:06. The Gauchos (15-9) suffered their third straight loss despite 27 points from Alex Harris, which included 5-for-10 shooting from the 3-point line. He was the only Gaucho player who made more than half his shots. Paul Butorac added 18 points for Eastern Washington (13-14).
